Package: sintHiChIP
Title: A Software to Find Significant Interactions in HiChIP Data
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Weiyue", "Ding", , "wyding0501@hotmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: 'sintHiChIP' is a robust and user-friendly R package designed to streamline the analysis of HiChIP (Hi-C chromatin immunoprecipitation) data. It offers a comprehensive pipeline from raw data processing to interaction map generation, supporting both local and global analysis modes. 'sintHiChIP' is built to facilitate the identification and visualization of significant chromatin interactions, incorporating enzyme restriction cut site density correction to enhance accuracy. This makes 'sintHiChIP' an invaluable tool for researchers in the field of genomics.
License: GPL-3
